reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 4, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars For my boys
reviews.reviewText: I purchased two of these for my boys. They really love , especially its big enough for personal items. It is sturdy and durable. Will purchase again .

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 6, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Fits everything I need in a compact way
reviews.reviewText: I specifically looked for a toiletries bag with the length this one has and am pleased to say that it fit my stuff perfectly. It has some nice pockets on the inside and one on the outside that I keep forgetting about. You can use it as permanent storage for stuff, or only when traveling (what I do) and I’d say it’s very worth the purchase.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 14, 2024
reviews.reviewText: It's a super nice size and has a great variety of pockets and pouches. Fits all my makeup, lotion, soaps, and etc for trips. It really holds a lot! It's pretty water resistant which is a good addition. Only complaint is that one of interior zippers did pop off after a couple months of use. Will still continue to use it though and would recommend!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 31, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars perfect for weekenders
reviews.reviewText: this is honestly the best toiletry bag i've ever had. I go to the lake almost every weekend and this thing has some miles on it and its holding up great. the canvas is kind of thin but not too thin too where it affects its durability. i'm a big organization girl while traveling and the inner pockets are perfect for products that are taller and would normally take up more space. I honestly want another because it would be great for hair products if im going on longer trips. Perfect size for weekend everything and week long toiletries.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 2, 2024
reviews.reviewText: Good, thick material! A little larger than the average toiletries bag and had good mesh pockets on the inside for securing items

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 3, 2024
reviews.reviewText: Bought to go with a big duffle that matches. Holds a lot of items. Durable. I would buy again.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 3, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Not the Best, Not the Worst
reviews.reviewText: The bag this replaced, I travelled all over the world with for 25 years so I struggled to find the same one as it surely has been discontinued. What I loved about the other bag is the additional pockets and compartments, which this bag doesn’t have.The outside does have one zippered compartment but it’s a weird size so I do t find it useful. ThisMeans the bag really just has one large compartment inside so absolutely everything goes in and gets mixed up and jostled around.My old bag had a divider in the main compartment that could be folded down if you wanted to (I didn’t) and the size compartments were a little baggy so larger items would better fit (this one is snug fitting). The material is decent quality (it’s held up so far) and the same for the zipper (doesn’t seem very rugged but is also holding up so far.I’d rather have a different bag but isn’t worth the time and effort so I’ll stick with this one for a while.
